burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.agentactions

Class ObParamSGAgentAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.agentactions.SGAgentAction
      • burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.agentactions.ObParamSGAgentAction

  • public abstract class ObParamSGAgentAction
extends SGAgentAction
    If your SGAgentAction implementation is paramerterized to OO-MDP ObjectInstance references, you can subclass this SGAgentAction subclass to easily provide that functionality. The GroundedSGAgentAction instance associated with this action is ObParamSGAgentAction.GroundedObParamSGAgentAction, which implements the AbstractObjectParameterizedGroundedAction, since its parameters refer to OO-MDP ObjectInstance references.

    The string array in the ObParamSGAgentAction(burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.SGDomain, String, String[]) constructor specifies the valid type of ObjectClass to which the parameters must belong.

    It may also be the case that the order of parameters for an ObjectParameterizedAction is unimportant. In this case, you can specify parameter order groups to indicate for which parameters the order is unimportant. See the ObjectParameterizedAction class documentation for more information of parameter order groups.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan.
